      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "I understand why you want peer specific, but this is not a good argument for removing flags used \r\n in the wild. `whitebind` and `whitelist` are not counter intuitive and useful as it simplify the configuration.\r\n\r\nAlso `whitelist` is a pain in the ass to use, in docker environment for example, we don't know beforehand the subnet IP, so `whitebind` is more useful.",
